         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>To our <supplied reason="lost">Lord</supplied> the unconquered and most noble Caesar, Flavius Valerius Severus; the Lepcitanians, 
               devoted to his divine power and majesty, <supplied reason="subaudible">set this up</supplied> publicly.</p></div>
         
         <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Al nostro signore, Cesare invitto e nobilissimo, Flavio Valerio Severo, i Leptitani, devoti al suo nume e alla sua maestà, a
               spese pubbliche</p></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#lsa" xml:lang="en"><p>To our lord, the unconquered and most noble Caesar, Flavius Valerius Severus; 
            the people of Lepcis (Lepcitani), devoted to his divine spirit and majesty, [set this up] with public funds.</p></div>
